-- Sberbank’s Pay for Board Members Jumps by 32 Percent, IFX Says
-- B y   J a s o n   C o r c o r a n
-- 2012-02-14T20:04:22Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-02-14/sberbank-s-pay-for-board-members-jumps-by-32-percent-ifx-says.html
OAO Sberbank (SBER) ,  Russia ’s largest bank,
increased the level of pay for its board members last year by 32
percent, Interfax reported, citing the lender’s news service.  The overall pay for the board members rose to 1.96 billion
rubles ($65 million) from 1.48 billion rubles in 2010, the news
agency said. The rise was connected to the lender’s jump in
profit, Interfax reported, citing Sberbank’s news service.  To contact the reporter on this story:
